The paper focuses on the empirical study of software engineering processes using data from software repositories, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of text mining techniques to extract fine-grained co-editing networks, which relates to social network analysis (cs.SI) and data mining (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of directed, weighted, and time-stamped networks, which relates to graph theory (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
